+# AI Tool Demo Production Kit
+
+**Owner:** AISignalOS  
+**Purpose:** A repeatable system for planning, scripting, recording, and publishing AI tool demo videos — faster and more consistently.  
+**Label:** All workflows marked `[SIMULATED]` require manual recording. Nothing here was live-executed against real AI tools.
+
+---
+
+## What This Kit Does
+
+Claude Code handles:
+- Demo planning and scripting
+- Voiceover copy
+- Shot lists and B-roll prompts
+- Thumbnail briefs
+- Captions, titles, descriptions
+- Sellable asset packaging
+- Scoring and evaluation frameworks
+
+You handle:
+- Hitting record (OBS, Loom, QuickTime, asciinema)
+- Running the actual AI tool
+- Speaking the voiceover
+- Editing the video
+
+---
+
+## Folder Map
+
+```
+demo-production-kit/
+  README.md                          ← this file
+  obs-recording-setup.md             ← OBS configuration for AI tool demos
+  demo-workflow-template.md          ← step-by-step template for any new demo
+  ai-tool-test-scorecard.md          ← evaluation sheet per tool
+  screen-recording-shot-list.md      ← reusable shot list template
+  voiceover-script-template.md       ← script structure for 60s and 3-min videos
+  caption-and-title-template.md      ← platform-specific copy templates
+  thumbnail-brief-template.md        ← art direction for thumbnails
+  asset-folder-structure.md          ← how to organize every demo's files
+  post-recording-edit-checklist.md   ← what to do after you stop recording
+
+  backlog/
+    ai-tool-demo-backlog.md          ← 15 tools, each with full demo plan
+
+  rating-framework/
+    ai-tool-rating-framework.md      ← 10-dimension scoring system
+
+  sample-demo/
+    canva-ai-demo-plan.md            ← fully written Canva AI demo (ready to record)
+```
+
+---
+
+## How to Use This Kit for a New Tool
+
+1. Copy `demo-workflow-template.md` → rename to `[tool-name]-demo-plan.md` in `sample-demo/`
+2. Fill in the tool-specific fields (angle, hook, workflow, script)
+3. Copy `ai-tool-test-scorecard.md` → score the tool after recording
+4. Set up OBS using `obs-recording-setup.md`
+5. Follow `screen-recording-shot-list.md` while recording
+6. Use `voiceover-script-template.md` to write or adapt the script
+7. After recording, run through `post-recording-edit-checklist.md`
+8. Use `caption-and-title-template.md` and `thumbnail-brief-template.md` to finish publishing assets
+
+---
+
+## Demo Backlog — 15 Tools
+
+See `backlog/ai-tool-demo-backlog.md` for the full list:
+
+| # | Tool         | Status     |
+|---|--------------|------------|
+| 1 | ChatGPT      | Planned    |
+| 2 | Claude       | Planned    |
+| 3 | Perplexity   | Planned    |
+| 4 | Gemini       | Planned    |
+| 5 | Canva AI     | **Ready** (sample demo written) |
+| 6 | Gamma        | Planned    |
+| 7 | HeyGen       | Planned    |
+| 8 | Runway       | Planned    |
+| 9 | Zapier AI    | Planned    |
+|10 | Make AI      | Planned    |
+|11 | ElevenLabs   | Planned    |
+|12 | Descript     | Planned    |
+|13 | Notion AI    | Planned    |
+|14 | Airtable AI  | Planned    |
+|15 | Replit Agent | Planned    |
+
+---
+
+## Ground Rules
+
+- Never claim a tool was live-tested unless you actually ran it.
+- Never publish, subscribe, or spend money using these scripts alone.
+- Always label simulated content with `[SIMULATED]`.
+- Keep raw recordings before editing — label them clearly.
