+# Demo Workflow Template
+
+Copy this file for each new AI tool demo. Replace all `[PLACEHOLDER]` values.  
+**Label:** Mark `[SIMULATED]` on any section not yet live-recorded.
+
+---
+
+## 1 — Overview
+
+| Field             | Value                    |
+|-------------------|--------------------------|
+| Tool name         | [TOOL NAME]              |
+| Tool URL          | [URL]                    |
+| Demo date         | [YYYY-MM-DD]             |
+| Recorded by       | [NAME]                   |
+| Status            | Planned / Recorded / Published |
+| Label             | [SIMULATED] or Live      |
+
+---
+
+## 2 — Demo Angle
+
+> One sentence: what specific capability are you demonstrating?
+
+[E.g. "Show how [Tool] can generate a full marketing email in under 60 seconds using only a product name and target audience."]
+
+---
+
+## 3 — Audience Pain Point
+
+> What problem does your viewer have that this demo solves?
+
+[E.g. "They spend hours writing marketing copy manually and don't know AI tools can do it in seconds."]
+
+---
+
+## 4 — Hook (First 3–5 seconds)
+
+**Short-form hook (spoken on camera or as text overlay):**
+> "[HOOK LINE — make a bold claim or ask a question that creates tension]"
+
+**Example structure:**
+- Bold claim: "This AI tool just replaced my [job task] — here's how."
+- Question: "What if you could [do X] in 60 seconds?"
+- Contrast: "Everyone uses [common tool] for this. I switched to [new tool] and here's why."
+
+---
+
+## 5 — Test Workflow
+
+Step-by-step of exactly what you will do on screen. Keep it tight — 3 to 6 steps max for short-form, up to 10 for long-form.
+
+**[SIMULATED — replace with actual recorded steps]**
+
+1. Open [TOOL URL] in Chrome
+2. [Action 1]
+3. [Action 2]
+4. [Action 3]
+5. Show the result / output
+6. Compare or evaluate
+
+---
+
+## 6 — What to Record
+
+| Shot                        | Scene (OBS)         | Notes                            |
+|-----------------------------|---------------------|----------------------------------|
+| Intro / hook                | Scene 2 (face cam)  | 3–5 seconds, look at camera      |
+| Tool homepage               | Scene 1 (browser)   | Show the UI clearly              |
+| Input / prompt entry        | Scene 4 (zoom)      | Zoom in on the text field        |
+| Output / result             | Scene 1 or 4        | Let it load fully before cutting |
+| Reaction / commentary       | Scene 2 (face cam)  | Brief, genuine reaction          |
+| CTA / outro                 | Scene 5 (card)      | 3–5 seconds                      |
+
+---
+
+## 7 — What to Say
+
+> Speak naturally from these bullet points — don't read word for word.
+
+**Intro:**
+- [What the tool is, one sentence]
+- [The pain point it solves]
+
+**During demo:**
+- [Narrate what you're doing and why it matters]
+- [Call out any surprising or impressive moments]
+- [Note limitations or caveats honestly]
+
+**Outro:**
+- [Your verdict in one sentence]
+- [CTA — subscribe / link in bio / next video]
+
+See `voiceover-script-template.md` for the full script structure.
+
+---
+
+## 8 — Evaluation Criteria
+
+Score the tool using `ai-tool-test-scorecard.md` after recording. Key dimensions:
+
+- Ease of use (1–5)
+- Output quality (1–5)
+- Speed (1–5)
+- Practical business value (1–5)
+- Free plan generosity (1–5)
+
+---
+
+## 9 — Asset / Product Angle
+
+> What can you create or sell off the back of this demo?
+
+- [ ] Free checklist / cheat sheet (lead magnet)
+- [ ] Paid tutorial / mini-course module
+- [ ] Prompt template pack
+- [ ] Comparison video (this tool vs. competitor)
+- [ ] Workflow template
+
+---
+
+## 10 — CTA (Call to Action)
+
+**Primary CTA:**
+> [E.g. "Subscribe for a new AI tool review every week."]
+
+**Secondary CTA:**
+> [E.g. "Download the free prompt pack — link in bio / description."]
+
+**Pinned comment:**
+> [Tool URL] | [Free resource link] | [Next video topic]
+
