+# Voiceover Script Template
+
+Use this structure for every AI tool demo script. Fill in the bracketed fields.  
+**Label:** `[SIMULATED]` — scripts require manual recording. Nothing is auto-narrated.
+
+---
+
+## Tone Guidelines
+
+- **Direct.** No "um", "so", "basically", "you know".
+- **Confident but honest.** Don't oversell. If a tool has limits, say so.
+- **Developer/creator-to-creator.** Peer, not professor.
+- **Specific.** Name the exact feature. Name the exact result. Use numbers.
+- **Fast but breathable.** Target ~150 words/minute for long-form, ~160–180 for short-form.
+
+---
+
+## Long-Form Script (3–10 minutes)
+
+---
+
+### HOOK (0:00–0:10)
+
+> "[One bold sentence that creates immediate tension or curiosity.]"
+
+Example: "I tested [TOOL] for a week so you don't have to — here's whether it's actually worth using."
+
+**Delivery:** Camera. No intro music yet. Just voice + face or screen.
+
+---
+
+### INTRO (0:10–0:30)
+
+> "[Tool name] is a [category] tool that [core promise]. Today I'm going to [specific test] and show you [specific result]."
+
+**Notes:** Short. Viewers skip long intros. Get to the demo fast.
+
+---
+
+### SETUP / CONTEXT (0:30–1:00)
+
+> "To test this, I'm going to [describe your test scenario]. I'm using the [free / paid] plan. No special settings — just out of the box."
+
+**Notes:**
+- State your plan (free/paid) — it affects what viewers can replicate.
+- State what you're testing — sets expectation.
+- "Out of the box" builds credibility.
+
+---
+
+### DEMO SECTION 1 — [MAIN FEATURE] (1:00–[X]:00)
+
+> "First, [action]. I'm going to [describe what you're doing on screen]."
+
+> "I'll type: '[your exact prompt or input]'"
+
+> "[Brief pause — let the tool run — narrate what's happening]"
+
+> "And here's the result. [Read or describe the output]. [Your reaction in one sentence.]"
+
+**Notes:**
+- Speak slowly over the output so viewers can read it.
+- If impressive: "That's actually pretty good for a first try."
+- If mediocre: "It works, but I'd need to [edit / refine / try again]."
+
+---
+
+### DEMO SECTION 2 — [SECOND FEATURE OR EDGE CASE] (optional)
+
+> "Now let me try something harder / more specific / that I'd actually use in my business."
+
+> "[Narrate the second test the same way.]"
+
+---
+
+### SCORE / EVALUATION ([X]:00–[X]:30)
+
+> "Here's how I'd score [TOOL]:
+
+> Ease of use: [X]/5 — [one sentence why].  
+> Output quality: [X]/5 — [one sentence why].  
+> Free plan: [X]/5 — [one sentence why].  
+> Overall: [X]/5."
+
+> "[Your verdict in one sentence.]"
+
+---
+
+### CTA / OUTRO ([X]:30–end)
+
+> "Full breakdown and [free resource] are linked below. Subscribe if you want [next tool] next week."
+
+---
+
+## Short-Form Script (60 seconds — TikTok / Reels / Shorts)
+
+**Word count target:** 130–160 words
+
+---
+
+```
+[HOOK — 1 sentence, 3–5 seconds]
+"[Bold claim or question about the tool]"
+
+[SETUP — 1 sentence]
+"I'm testing [TOOL] to see if it can [specific task]."
+
+[INPUT — narrate what you're typing]
+"I type: '[prompt]'"
+
+[RESULT — describe output]
+"[Describe the result in 1–2 sentences. Be specific.]"
+
+[REACTION — 1 honest sentence]
+"[Your genuine take — good, bad, or nuanced.]"
+
+[SCORE — fast]
+"[X]/5 for [dimension]. [X]/5 overall."
+
+[CTA — 1 sentence]
+"[Follow / subscribe / link in bio for full breakdown.]"
+```
+
+---
+
+## On-Screen Text Overlay Plan
+
+| Timestamp | Text to display                     | Style          |
+|-----------|-------------------------------------|----------------|
+| 0:03      | [TOOL NAME]                         | Large, bold    |
+| 0:10      | "[Pain point or hook]"              | Subtitle       |
+| 0:25      | "My prompt: [exact input]"          | Caption box    |
+| 0:35      | "Result ↓"                          | Arrow + text   |
+| 0:48      | "[SCORE] / 5"                       | Score badge    |
+| 0:55      | "Full review → link in bio"         | CTA chip       |
+
+---
+
+## Delivery Notes
+
+| Moment                     | Delivery tip                                           |
+|----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
+| Hook                       | Look at lens. No smile yet. Create tension.            |
+| Typing the prompt          | Slow down. Describe what you're typing.                |
+| Waiting for generation     | Don't go silent — narrate the wait or cut it.         |
+| Showing the result         | React genuinely before speaking.                       |
+| Giving a score             | Pause between each score. Let it land.                 |
+| CTA                        | Smile. Look at lens. Mean it.                          |
